"title": "SCREENING ‚Äî for a patient to schedule a screening appointment",
"body": "for a patient to schedule a screening appointment\n     ‚óè‚Äã screening to become a comprehensive patient is by appointment only\n     ‚óè‚Äã to schedule a screening, the potential patient should call: (312) 996-1265\n              ‚óã‚Äã the screening phone line is open Monday through Friday at 9:30 AM and remains open until all appointments are\n                   filled, usually ending at 1:30 pm\n     ‚óè‚Äã screening appointments are offered during both morning and afternoon sessions\nscreening family members / planning a screening with a specific patient\n    1.‚Äã send pt to registration (1st floor) ‚Üí pt should tell front desk that they have a student in [clinic] who will be screening them\n    2.‚Äã after they have been registered (they have an Axium number), registration will send them to the 2nd floor to fill out a\n        screening sheet with Mickey\n    3.‚Äã after they have filled out the screening sheet, you will call them in & screen them\nscreening: equipment\n    ‚óè‚Äã from locker: loupes and/or eye protection\n    ‚óè‚Äã in clinic: disposable plastic mirror\nscreening: steps\n    1.‚Äã seat patient\n             ‚óã‚Äã get the patient from the waiting room & seat them in the assistant chair next to you\n    2.‚Äã go through screening sheet\n             ‚óã‚Äã write chief complaint, in the pt‚Äôs own words, on the screening sheet\n             ‚óã‚Äã review the patient‚Äôs medical history that they‚Äôve written on the screening sheet (do not enter anything in Axium)\n    3.‚Äã explain school policies\n             ‚óã‚Äã explain how the appointments work!!!\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã appointments will generally last 3 hours\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã the patient will require 4 initial appointments (radiographs, perio COE, restorative COE, treatment plan)\n                          before any treatment will be started ‚Äî warn them that these appointments will last 3 hours each (they\n                          may be shorter, but sometimes they do take the whole time)\n             ‚óã‚Äã comprehensive & sequenced treatment is required\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã we cannot just do the 1 crown the patient wants, we have to treat the whole mouth in proper tx. order\n             ‚óã‚Äã all payment is required at the beginning of treatment\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã the school does not accept payment plans\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã the patient will not need to pay for the entire treatment plan at the first appointment; they pay as they go\n                          for the treatment they will be having that day\n             ‚óã‚Äã the patient needs to keep their scheduled appointments\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã less than 24 hours notice to cancel/reschedule an appointment counts as a failed appointment\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã if the patient fails their first appointment, they will be dismissed\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã if the patient fails 3 appointments, they will be dismissed\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã if a patient cannot keep an appointment, they need to notify at least 24 hours before\n             ‚óã‚Äã a patient cannot bring their children under 14 with them to their appointment\n             ‚óã‚Äã it may take 6-8 weeks for the patient to be assigned to a student (exception: if you‚Äôre accepting the patient for\n                 yourself right now, they‚Äôre assigned usually within 2 weeks)\n    4.‚Äã perform oral exam\n             ‚óã‚Äã move the patient to the dental chair & take a super fast look in their mouth (use a plastic mirror in the unit)\n             ‚óã‚Äã on the screening sheet, circle what types of care the patient will require\n    5.‚Äã approve patient\n             ‚óã‚Äã D0147 (screening N/C)\n             ‚óã‚Äã before planning the 3 codes below, check Dexis to see if pt already has FMX or pan; then ask patient if they‚Äôve had\n                 FMX or pan recently & are able to acquire it (you won‚Äôt need to plan these codes then)\n             ‚óã‚Äã plan (P) 3 codes:\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã D0150 (COE)\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã D0330 (Panoramic film)\n                     ‚ñÝ‚Äã D0210 (Intraoral - complete series)\n             ‚óã‚Äã write your note now before your instructor comes over\n    6.‚Äã present the patient to instructor\n             ‚óã‚Äã make sure the instructor signs the screening sheet\n\n              ‚óã‚Äã have the instructor swipe your codes/note\n    7.‚Äã if pt is not approved\n              ‚óã‚Äã if the patient is not approved, provide the appropriate referrals (providers outside UIC, GPR list, UIC PG programs)\n                        ‚ñÝ‚Äã you can get a sheet of paper that has the referral list from your clinic manager / in your clinic\n              ‚óã‚Äã if patient is being referred to a UIC PG clinic, complete a referral through Axium\n    8.‚Äã take patient to radiology\n              ‚óã‚Äã take the patient to radiology to have them take a panoramic x-ray same day (they can schedule it for later if they\n                   don‚Äôt want to take it today)\n                        ‚ñÝ‚Äã take off your gown before you go down to radiology\n                        ‚ñÝ‚Äã you will need the patient‚Äôs Axium number, so bring the screening sheet\n                        ‚ñÝ‚Äã the patient may also get the FMX taken that day if radiology has an opening (usually they are booked); the\n                            patient may choose to come back & schedule the FMX for another day (they aren‚Äôt required to get the\n                            FMX same day)\n              ‚óã‚Äã once the patient is done checking in with radiology, you can leave & return to your clinic, and the patient can leave\n                   after they‚Äôve taken their x-rays (or after scheduling, if they don‚Äôt want to take x-rays same day)\n    9.‚Äã return screening sheet to Mickey\n              ‚óã‚Äã if you want the patient assigned to you, write ‚ÄúPlease assign patient to [name]‚Äù on bottom of the screening sheet\nscreening: note template\n  y/o female presents to UIC COD for screening appointment. Pt‚Äôs CC: ‚Äú .‚Äù Reviewed medical history. Performed oral inspection. Explained college\n policies, including attendance, transportation, & financial policy. Patient is provisionally accepted to UG clinic.\n\n Planned COE, FMX, pan.\n\n NV: COE"
