"body": "test            what does it detect?               how to record results               results are consistent with              other potential explanations\n\n                                                                                       - normal: 2s / 2s (patient feels cold,\n                                                                                       feeling does not linger)\n                                                                                        - reversible pulpitis: 0.5 s/3 s        - false positive: cotton pellet\n                                                   x s. / x s.\n                a pulp test ‚Äî differentiates                                           (stronger, painful, quicker              touches adjacent teeth, anxious\n                                                        ‚Ü≥ duration until response,\ncold test       between normal, inflamed, &                                            response, does not significantly         patients respond preemptively\n                                                        duration of linger\n                necrotic pulp                                                          linger)                                  - false negative: pulp chamber\n                                                   NR if no response\n                                                                                       - symptomatic irreversible pulpitis:     calcification, not enough Endo Ice\n                                                                                       0.5 s / 20s (stronger, painful,\n                                                                                       quicker response that lingers)\n\n                a pulp test ‚Äî differentiates\n                                                                                                                                - false negative: pulp chamber\nEPT             between normal, inflamed, &        #                                   - 80 = necrotic pulp\n                                                                                                                                calcification, pulpal recession\n                necrotic pulp\n\n                                                   ‚Äì = not tender                                                               - high restoration, parafunctional\n                                                   + = mildly tender                                                            habits, blunt trauma, advanced\npercussion      inflammation of the PDL                                                - symptomatic apical periodontitis\n                                                   ++ = moderately tender                                                       periodontal disease, sinusitis,\n                                                   +++ = severely tender                                                        orthodontics\n\n                                                   ‚Äì = not tender\n                inflammation of the PDL            + = mildly tender                   - cracked tooth/root with vital pulp\nbite test                                                                                                                                        ‚Äî\n                replicates CC of ‚Äúchewing pain‚Äù    ++ = moderately tender              - faulty restoration\n                                                   +++ = severely tender\n\n                                                   ‚Äì = not tender\n                                                                                       - necrotic pulp                          - gingival conditions (herpes,\n                                                   + = mildly tender\n                                                                                       - apical periodontitis                   aphthous ulcers), trauma\npalpation       inflammation of the periosteum     ++ = moderately tender\n                                                                                       - apical abscess: fluctuant area or      - in posterior maxilla, sinus\n                                                   +++ = severely tender\n                                                                                       pus                                      inflammation\n                                                   also indicate location\n\n                                                   0 = no mobility\n                                                                                                                                - periodontal disease, trauma,\n                                                   1 = less than 1 mm BL\nmobility        loss of supporting alveolar bone                                       - necrotic pulp                          parafunctional habits, crown\n                                                   2 = 1+ mm BL\n                                                                                                                                fracture\n                                                   3 = 1+ mm BL and vertical\n\n                                                                                       - a narrow, deep probing depth\n                                                                                       (esp. on proximal surface of\n                                                                                       posterior tooth) is consistent with\nprobing depth   tooth fractures                    in mm                               crown/root fracture                      - periodontal disease\n                                                                                       - narrow, deep probing depth may\n                                                                                       be a sinus tract ‚Üí apical abscess,\n                                                                                       necrotic pulp\n\n                a pulp test ‚Äî differentiates       x s. / x s.                          - rarely performed; only performed\nhot test        between normal, inflamed, &        duration until response, duration of when patient‚Äôs chief complaint is                        ‚Äî\n                necrotic pulp                      linger                               heat\n\n                a pulp test ‚Äî differentiates\n                                                   NR ‚Äî no response                    - rarely performed\ntest cavity     between normal, inflamed, &                                                                                                      ‚Äî\n                                                   pain upon test cavity               - no response ‚Üí necrotic pulp\n                necrotic pulp"
